                      <span>2004-05-17</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I anxiously awaited the release of this book, as well as the other two in the series. What a disappointment! There is nothing in this book that is new or exciting. Kate offers the same old, tired suggestions that you can find in any book on entertaining. The watercolor illustrations are cute but that's about it. This book has no substance and reads more like a children's book then anything else. For $20 these books are overpriced, as is anything with the Kate Spade name on it. Don't waste your hard-earned money so she and her yuppy husband can laugh all the way to the bank, or their "summer home" in the Hamptons! :-(</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">YES!</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
